node.text:
On this episode of Old Flames New Flames we head all the way to New Zealand to visit @MadMike.123 at his MADLAB headquarters.⁣
⁣
More than just a pro drifter and Mazda maniac, Mad Mike is an internationally known car culture personality known for building cars that sound as radical as they look.⁣
⁣
Mad Mike takes us back to his childhood days, playing with Hot Wheels tracks and encountering an unforgettable Mazda RX-4,⁣ which has had him hooked on rotary engines ever since.⁣
⁣
He then shows us some of the coolest cars in his garage, from his legendary MADBUL FD RX-7 drift car to the Mazda MX-5 that he recently built as family project with⁣ his son.⁣
⁣
He also talks about some his most memorable Hot Wheels die-cast collaborations, including his PITBUL Mazda pickup truck and the latest Hot Wheels x Mad Mike release - a classic Mazda RX-3 that’s been given the Treasure⁣ Hunt treatment. #HotWheels⁣

node.title: Old Flames, New Flames: Mad Mike

node.text:
As part of Hot Wheels’ celebration of Black History Month we present a special episode of Old Flames/New Flames where we stop by @Bisimoto Engineering in Southern California to talk with founder Bisi Ezerioha about his history of speed and his collaborations with Hot Wheels.⁣
⁣
How does one go from tinkering on a humble little Honda CRX to building some of the wildest, highest horsepower street and track cars in the world? Hear it from the man himself. ⁣
⁣
Bisi tells us about his start in the industry and goes through some of his favorite cars and most notable builds - from a 1,000 horsepower minivan to a Porsche 935s with a full electric powertrain.⁣
⁣
He also tells us about the experience of having his first project car immortalized as a Hot Wheels die-cast and about his experience on real life car builds inspired by Hot Wheels.⁣
⁣
Few people have reimagined vehicles the way Bisi has. Come with us as we take a trip  through the mind of one of today’s most forward-thinking car builders. #HotWheels #BlackHistoryMonth

node.title: Old Flames, New Flames: Bisi Ezerioha

When it comes to the world of JDM tuning, few names are more respected than @GreddyKenji - whether it’s in Japan, in California or anywhere else in the world.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Kenji Sumino is the president of @GReddyPerformance Products in Southern California and as you might expect he’s a mega gearhead, whose personal cars are just as cool as the ones his company builds.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We visited Kenji to chat about real cars and die-cast cars and asked him about his history with Hot Wheels - both as a kid growing up and the GReddy x Hot Wheels collaborations he’s been part of in recent years.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Kenji talks about some his most memorable builds that have immortalized in Hot Wheels forms, including the FuguZ Datsun he did with actor Sung Kang and he also shows us his own restored and modified EF Honda Civic hatchback which he calls his real life “Treasure Hunt” car.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Finally, Kenji shows us a preview the latest collaboration with Hot Wheels and GReddy - legendary JDM race machine⁣⁣ wearing the name of an equally legendary tuning brand.⁣ #HotWheels

node.title: Old Flames, New Flames: Kenji Sumino

node.text:
@MagnusWalker also known as “The Urban Outlaw” is a man just as recognizable as the cars he builds and drives. 

We recently got together with Magnus at his downtown LA headquarters to talk about his automotive history which started with a humble old Toyota Corolla and grew into one of the world’s most impressive car collections. 

He also goes through his long-time interest in Hot Wheels, and talks about some of his favorite Hot Wheels collaborations over the years. Even in miniaturized diecast form, his unique Urban Outlaw style has made itself well known. 

And while he’s best know for his obsession with Porsche, Magnus introduces us to some of his other recent additions as well, which include everything from a funky 1970s AMC to a classic Jaguar E-Type. 

Keen eyes will also see Magnus give us a sneak peek at his latest Hot Wheels diecast collaboration which will be hitting stores shelves soon, and he even shows us the real life car that inspired it.

node.title: Old Flames, New Flames: Magnus Walker

node.text:
Congratulations to @mitten_customs and their radical, snakeskin green Dodge Viper! Thanks to your votes, they're taking home the  @mobil1 Fan Favorite award from the latest Legends Tour stop in Detroit, MI.⁣
⁣
This eye-popping build looks fast standing still thanks to an immaculately executed custom 1 of 6, A10 wide body with custom wheels. This vehicle is a vibe all around, especially when you step inside to see a luxurious galaxy headliner. #goals ⁣
⁣
It's not all show with the Mitten Customs Viper. Under the hood it packs a punch with 1340 hp thanks to a Calvo Motorsports 1300 twin turbo package. Talk about a dream car! Now who wants to see this thing rip?!⁣

PS: Don't forget to tune in on 8/26 for the next stop of the Hot Wheels Legends Tour when we go VIRTUAL on Facebook Live with @Speedsociety!

#HotWheelsLegends 
⁣

Always big on style and expression drifting has continuously evolved. As it’s moved into new regions, new vehicles could be found in the mix.  In America, it was naturally V8 engines and iconic muscle cars that’d become big parts of the drift scene.

Congratulations to Josh Liem  and Corinne Currie and their 1975 Opel Manta for taking home the win in Detroit!💪🏎

With so many rad cars rolling through yesterday, this was not an easy choice. This little blue Manta was bought as a shell for $1000 and transformed to a full blown dirt track/street car in just 6 months! 

It checked off all the boxes: 
✅Creativity ✅Authenticity ✅Garage Spirit. ⁣
But what do you think? Would you like to see this build transformed into a Hot Wheels? 

#HotWheelsLegends
